===动机===

====被用作从震惊和恐惧中获得地位和宣传的手段====
历史学家蒂莫西·弗内什等人认为斩首是恐怖组织使用的战术，以此来造成最大限度的震惊以及向外界表明他们的组织正在逐渐壮大<ref name="meforum.org">[http://www.meforum.org/713/beheading-in-the-name-of-islam] {{Wayback|url=http://www.meforum.org/713/beheading-in-the-name-of-islam |date=20210204202001 }} Beheading in the Name of Islam, Timothy R. Furnish, Middle East Quarterly, Spring 2005.</ref><ref>[http://articles.sun-sentinel.com/2004-06-24/news/0406240096_1_beheading-hostages-saudi-arabia] {{Wayback|url=http://articles.sun-sentinel.com/2004-06-24/news/0406240096_1_beheading-hostages-saudi-arabia |date=20160304071421 }} New Tactic In Terror: Beheading Of Hostages; Images On Internet Meant To Shock World, Win Recruits, Tim Collie, 24 June 2004, Sun Sentinel.</ref><ref>[http://www.au.af.mil/au/awc/awcgate/ssi/terr_beheadings.pdf] {{Wayback|url=http://www.au.af.mil/au/awc/awcgate/ssi/terr_beheadings.pdf |date=20170502004830 }}  Terrorist Beheadings: Cultural and Strategic Implications, United States Department of the Air Force, RH Jones, 2005.</ref> 然而，西方的观察家{{which|date=September 2014}}也认为基地组织的斩首策略适得其反，穆斯林对其残暴行径的畏缩而导致了集团的衰败。<ref>[http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/middleeast/syria/11071276/Where-does-the-Islamic-States-fetish-with-beheading-people-come-from.html] {{Wayback|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/middleeast/syria/11071276/Where-does-the-Islamic-States-fetish-with-beheading-people-come-from.html |date=20201208135039 }} Where does the Islamic State's fetish with beheading people come from?
Terror group's tactics create fear out of all proportion to its military size, Shashank Joshi, 2 September 2014, Telegraph.</ref>

在2005年7月18日，两名武装分子冲击了[[泰国南部地区|泰国南部地区]]的一家茶馆，将佛教徒Lek Pongpla斩首，将他的头颅留在店门外。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.terrorism.com/2005/07/18/47855/ |title=Beheadings Raise Tensions in Thailand |access-date=2015-04-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141211091843/http://www.terrorism.com/2005/07/18/47855/ |archive-date=2014-12-11 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>

====被用作招募工具====
根据{{le|彼得·R·诺伊曼|Peter R. Neumann}}博士的说法，病毒式的斩首视频多少都对招募西方和中东的圣战者起了作用。<ref>[http://www.chicagotribune.com/news/nationworld/chi-foley-pearl-islamist-beheadings-20140821-story.html] {{WebCite|url=https://www.webcitation.org/6SlAVEQLl?url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/news/nationworld/chi-foley-pearl-islamist-beheadings-20140821-story.html |date=20140921184436 |dateformat=iso }} From Daniel Pearl to James Foley: The modern tactic of Islamist beheadings, Adam Taylor, 21 August 2014, Washington Post/Chicago Tribune.</ref><ref name="csmonitor.com">[http://www.csmonitor.com/World/Security-Watch/terrorism-security/2014/0829/Islamic-State-steps-up-propaganda-videos-beheading-another-captive] {{Wayback|url=http://www.csmonitor.com/World/Security-Watch/terrorism-security/2014/0829/Islamic-State-steps-up-propaganda-videos-beheading-another-captive |date=20190727215710 }} Islamic State steps up propaganda videos, beheading another captive, Videotaped atrocities in an attempt to spread fear are nothing new for IS. But it appears to be stepping up its propaganda as world powers start to engage in halting its spread, Dan Murphy, 29 August 2014, Christian Science Monitor.</ref>其他观察人士认为，虽然[[基地组织|基地组织]]最初用斩首作为宣传工具，可后来才意识到这样做适得其反。[[伊斯兰国|伊斯兰国]](ISIS)在2014年积极展开斩首策略，可能也察觉到了将斩首作为策略的弊端。<ref>[http://nymag.com/daily/intelligencer/2014/08/why-beheading-videos-are-back-with-isis.html] {{Wayback|url=http://nymag.com/daily/intelligencer/2014/08/why-beheading-videos-are-back-with-isis.html |date=20170424202630 }} Why Beheading Videos Are Back With ISIS, and Why They Went Away, Katie Zavadski, 21 August 2014, New York Magazine.</ref>

